        rather than installing something unverified: the console holds the PVE
        credentials and the fleet CA, so an unchecked binary there is not a
        partial failure, it is the whole trust chain.

        Build (from the qubes-air repo, CGO_ENABLED=1 is required — go-sqlite3
        is cgo, and CGO_ENABLED=0 compiles cleanly then dies at runtime with
        unknown driver "sqlite3"):
          cd console/backend
          CGO_ENABLED=1 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o qubes-air-console ./cmd/server
          sha256sum qubes-air-console
    -#}
    # From the artifact store, like the agent .deb, terraform and the provider.
    # Staging it in the salt tree also works (salt://qubesair/files/...) but puts
    # an 18MB build artifact through scripts/setup.sh on every deploy.
    # Built with CGO_ENABLED=1 for linux/amd64 -- see salt/qubesair/files/README.md
    # for why both of those, and --platform, are load-bearing on an arm64 Mac.
